Compounds N30 (N-(4-nitrophenyl methyl) benzothiazole-6-amine, Fig. 1a ) was originally provided by Professor Zhuorong Li at the Institute of Medicinal Bioechnology Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences, Beijing, China. Pirodavir (Biochempartner), oseltamivir carboxylate (OC, Medchem), amantadine hydrochloride (AH, Sigma-Aldrich) and Ribavirin (RBV, Sigma-Aldrich) were used as reference drugs in vitro. N30, pirodavir and AH were dissolved in dimethyl sulfoxide (DMSO, Sigm-Aldrich). OC and RBV were dissolved at phosphate buffered saline (PBS, Gbico). 